korari
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:flax (plant)
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: The plant itself (in the north).: anglicised in many forms, esp. in the SI: claddie, colladdy, kolladdy, koraddy, etc; the tall flower stem of the native flax; often the plant itself [Maori korari[o-macron]].
